I encountered this with libmodulemd - for example the 'profiles' properity of the Modulemd object: https://github.com/fedora-modularity/libmodulemd/blob/master/modulemd/modulemd-module.c#L3087

The code here used to be:

    g_value_set_boxed (value, modulemd_module_peek_profiles (self));

Which worked fine with pygobject-3.26 and earlier, but when that started crashing with pygobject-3.28, Stephen Gallagher changed it to:

    g_value_take_boxed (value, modulemd_module_dup_profiles (self));

which apparently worked - but doesn't really. The new GHashTable that is returned has key/value free functions, so if it wasn't leaked, the objects in it would be double-unreffed - once by pygobject, once by the value free function.

